This paper addresses issues related to verifiability and completeness of information in Wikipedia entity pages, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, the paper proposes automated approaches for improving the quality of textual knowledge bases, which is related to natural language processing (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and databases (cs.DB). The paper also suggests relevant and missing news references, which can be seen as a recommendation system (cs.AI) or a machine learning task (cs.LG).
